What is Marine Le Pen doing with her new popularity with the French white working class?
It wants to use next year's European elections to create a single anti-money and anti-European bloc in the European Parliament.
If the anti-European parties look good in these elections, which is very possible, such a bloc could control the European Parliament for the first time.
This is what I think: very soon, the anti-European and anti-currency sentiment unique in Europe will unite and will eventually kill the euro.
The EU will not disappear, but it will return to something that will look more like the "Europe of (sovereign) nations" free privileged by General de Gaulle.
Germany and some of its satellite economies could retain the euro, but France and southern Europe will return to their own currency.
I expect the UK to distance itself from this project, and I hope it will make the eyes soft in the United States.
However, Washington's growing interest in the Pacific suggests that Britain will be left behind in the Atlantic.
And Scotland in all this?
