Otherwise, we should imitate Norway and maintain our economic independence.
Scotland’s SNP government is – and it should be noted – the most successful anti-austerity political movement in Europe, as it won a spectacular majority in 2011 based on its opposition to the proposed (and implemented) dark cuts by Labour Chancellor Alistair Darling and the ensuing Conservative/Liberal-Democrat coalition.
