"Undoubtedly between 120 and 150 million all countries combined," he said last March.
His Burmese cat on his knees, in the living room of his huge apartment of a building on Avenue Foch close to the Arc de Triomphe, the malicious eye under his white hair, he cited some of the languages in which the adventures of SAS were translated: Italian, German, Russian, Greek, Japanese or Korean.
