At each book, the same recipe: a large dose of geopolitics and exoticism, some hard sex scenes, a zest of violence and torture.
"I never pretended to be a literary author," explained Gérard de Villiers.
I consider myself a storyteller who writes to distract people to whom I do not send a message.
He worked "like the great pre-war reporters, of the Albert London type, who went there and came back with real and long investigations."
SAS's father said "to make a kind of geopolitical soap opera."
